# EAS Build upload ignore list.
#
# Why: the repo contains committed native `android/` (and `ios/`) folders whose
# gradle build fails on EAS. Ignoring them here makes EAS treat this as a managed
# project and run a fresh `expo prebuild` from app.json on the build server —
# which uses the correct applicationId (com.tripsplitter.app, matching the Google
# OAuth client) and the splash asset, with no app-code change.
#
# NOTE: when a .easignore exists, EAS uses it INSTEAD of .gitignore for the upload,
# so this also mirrors the heavy/dev-only excludes to keep the upload small.

# Native projects — regenerated by `expo prebuild` on EAS
/android
/ios

# Dependencies & build output (reinstalled / regenerated on EAS)
node_modules/
.expo/
.expo-shared/
web-build/
dist/

# Local env & logs (build env comes from eas.json `env`, never .env)
.env
.env.*
*.log

# VCS / OS noise
.git/
.DS_Store
